        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Considering that Ophidian is brand new (doesn't even have the game yet) I would say...try a warrior for awhile.  It is quite a confusing world when you start out.  All necros are KoS (kill on sight) to some degree.  I remember getting stomped by guards my first day in Qeynos, way back when.  Being KoS is NOT for newbs.  If you are an experienced gamer, you might want to try a necro.  We are one of the most interesting classes in EQ.  </P><P>As to race: Iksar are ok for starting out, but unless you want to level up in Kunark the whole time, the KoS factor is HUGE for a newb in the old world.  Gnome would actually be a good choice.  They have some night vision, tolerated in their home city (and most other cities), Ak'anon takes a small while to get used to, but its not as bad as the other Necro locations (except maybe Freeport and Paineel).  </P><P>The nightvision thing should not be overlooked by a true newb.  I made a Human wizard way back when and ended up deleting him when I couldn't see my hand in front of my face at night.</P><P>/shrug</P><P>Try the gnome.</P><P> </font></td>
