 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Lizalfos</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> I know this will be beating a dead horse, but here goes anyways.  Since the changes to exp loss have been made, and you cannot lose exp until 12, who cares?  Make your necro and have fun.  That's what this game is about.  Make a necro, ask others in game for tips, be polite and have fun with it.  I would say 90% of the time people will respond to questions about how to do something.  Just be polite.  As far as starting int, who cares who gets more because + int items are incredably easy to get.  Personally I chose an Iksar and I noticed something.  I have 2 friends in an old guild I used to group with all the time.  Their played time is about 4 times what mine is, and there is a 2 level difference between us.  These two are a barbarian warrior and a barbie shammy.  You can argue the time it takes to go from 49 to 51 as much as you want, but simple truth is I will be 51 with less time than they did it.  Take this Iksar Necros word for it, the exp penalty is not really worth mentioning.  That being said, there is another reason for chosing Iksar.  We are the only race truely home on Kunark.  Think to the "noraml" levelling progression for Old world and Kunark.  Old World is race noob area, East Commons, North Ro, Oasis, Lake Of Ill Omen, Frontieer Mountains, Overthere, then Dreadlands or Velious, etc.  Kunark is typically Field of Bone, Kurns Tower, Lake Of Ill Omen, Frontieer Mountains, Overthere.  Your going to be on Kunark most likely from 15 till 35 or so, you might as well be home there.  KoS will only come in to play when you are in the Overthere as Iksar because of the Dragoons (guards) who roam the zone at night.  Really, the KoS bit takes effect after we have Harmshield (10 sec invinciability), Fiegn Death (self explanitory), invis (self Explanatory).  Faction has no real effect until we can do something about it.  However Sgt Slate in East Commons with Dark Elves is another story.  Using that as a starting off point is really pointless.  Lower starting int ok, it may hurt a tiny bit with reguards to raising skills in the beginning, but by level 25 or so you should be fine there.  Dark Elf &gt; Iksar in night vision, but Iksar is not night blind and the night has never been a problem for me.  I forget where the base resists are, but suffice it to say Dark Elf and Iksar are relatively balanced there (I know Iksar have a 35 fire resist but only a 15 cold resist, all others at 25).  When you are tanking, you have better AC than other classes (lower levels "&lt;15" only).  Regen does help a bit, and it really depends on what you have.  Post 50, it makes a huge difference in my opinion, then again, I have items to make me regain mana faster, so I need to be in Lich (hit points to mana) for less time to get to full mana.</P><P>I would personally leave the Erudite Necros out of it.  Just because they are really isolated in where they can hunt until level 8 (iksar can go to swamp of no hope, noob area in Lake of ill omen, noob area in warsliks woods, or field of bone).  In my opinion killing the same things over and over again just isn't worth the extra int they start with especially when int is so easily raised.  But the validity of that argument depends on what you think you will enjoy doing in game.</P><P>Gnomes, I know little about, and haven't played them.  I can't say much about them here.</P><P>Humans, well as to humans I can say only one thing.  They are middle of the road.  Not good not bad.  There is always a better choise for a certain class than the humans.</P><P>Dark Elves.  Here's where I will make some enemies.  I personally feel the city is too complicated for a low level.  3 zones for the city plus it is only easy to navigate to those who have been there before.  I found myself (before I knew about eqatlas.com) accidently zoning alot because I got turned around.  I am using the same int argument as I did about the erudites, and adding in that the young kodiaks will jump you in the noob area there.  Not a problem as you can easily kill them at level 12 when you will take an exp loss from death, but an annoyance anyways.  The quests are ok, and they do suffer faction problems I would consider much worse than the Iksar.  Try hunting Karnors or Howling Stones when on Kunark.  You will be KoS very quick to your outpost on Kunark.  Same will happen if you hunt the much less populated Kaesora.  3 zones with nice loot you cannot really hunt if you want to have a place you can easily and safely sell to on Kunark.  Otherwise, I have to disagree with an earlier comment about half the time your looking at a necro when looking at a dark elf.  Usually it is a chanter, at least for me, but that has no real point here.</P><P>Iksar.  Higher AC (that really only makes a difference when needed at lower levels), regeneration, and *most* players are going to be by you for grouping if you choose to do so post level 15 with no real need to even worry about KoS until the 30's or so, in my opinion make the Iksar an excellent choise for a necro.  However, you will hear people harp on the exp penalty Iksar have, but ask any Iksar Necro if they really noticed it and they will most likely say no.  While the Iksar Necro quests do, well, lets just say verant left the stick up there when  we were bent over getting it like all the other necros, there are at least original and seem to have a common theme.  There are only 2 things I would change about my race as a necro.  First, I would make me look like an Iksar Skele when I take on skele form, and 2nd, I would have a sign painted on me saying I am not an Enchanter, but an Iksar Necro.  Then again, I usually hunt with my afk message saying Iksar necro, not a chanter.  What chanter in their right mind would solo here?  So I guess it's not a big deal.</P><P>I tried to be as direct with why I made my choise as possible.  Hope this helps you and you enjoy your necro whatever race you choose.</P><P><BR>Lizalfos Deathscale</P><P>Edited by - Lizalfos on 07/19/2002  14:53:25</font></td>
      </tr>
